## Verification Workflow

For workflow_run_prompt_apply, source_type_allow_list must contain only exact source type keys from the Source type catalog in prompt context. Natural-language phrases such as all supported source types are not source type keys. Map clear natural-language source-scope instructions to exact source type keys from the prompt context. An unrestricted request for all source types must be represented by an empty source_type_allow_list. A source-scope instruction that clearly limits allowed source types must be represented in source_type_allow_list and must not remain only in shared_instruction. Product type values must be separated from shared_instruction: product_type_request_list owns requested product type phrases, and shared_instruction must not repeat those values.

For workflow_run_prompt_apply, priority_country_code must reflect the priority country requested in the workflow prompt as one ISO 3166 alpha-2 uppercase country code. The stage must not invent a default country when the workflow prompt does not choose one. The priority-country request must not remain duplicated in shared_instruction.

For workflow_run_prompt_apply, stage_instruction_list must contain only PromptStageInstruction objects extracted from exact stage instruction text in the workflow prompt. Verify that each stage-specific instruction uses an exact supported stage key, preserves the user's exact stage instruction meaning, and no longer remains duplicated in shared_instruction. Remove stage-specific instructions from shared_instruction is the required action-stage behavior; verification must fail when the result keeps one stage-specific instruction only in shared_instruction.

